01:19:37,511 --> 01:19:38,556
[SCREAMING]

1207
01:19:39,731 --> 01:19:41,080
My hand, man!

1208
01:19:41,211 --> 01:19:42,473
Where's Antoine Vallon?

1209
01:19:42,603 --> 01:19:43,517
You broke my hand, man!

1210
01:19:44,780 --> 01:19:46,999
I know you
remember me, Jerry.

1211
01:19:47,130 --> 01:19:48,305
[BONES CRACKING][SCREAMING]

1212
01:19:50,568 --> 01:19:51,438
Where's Vallon?

1213
01:19:51,569 --> 01:19:53,658
Wait a minute.

1214
01:19:53,789 --> 01:19:54,790
If I tell you where Vallon
is, he'll kill my wife
and kid, man.

1215
01:19:57,705 --> 01:20:00,491
Your wife left you in 2019
after filing charges
for domestic abuse.

1216
01:20:00,621 --> 01:20:01,927
And you don't have a kid.

1217
01:20:02,754 --> 01:20:03,624
But I do.

1218
01:20:03,755 --> 01:20:05,452
[SCREAMING]

1219
01:20:05,583 --> 01:20:07,193
I'm not askin' again!

1220
01:20:07,324 --> 01:20:09,413
Look, I swear, man.
I don't know where
Vallon is, okay?

1221
01:20:09,543 --> 01:20:12,851
The only guy I talk to
is his driver Marcus.
That's it, man. That's it!

1222
01:20:12,982 --> 01:20:14,679
Does he have a phone number?

1223
01:20:31,261 --> 01:20:34,612
We have a problem.
Alex is breaking protocol.

1224
01:20:34,742 --> 01:20:35,874
What's he doing?

1225
01:20:36,005 --> 01:20:37,876
He's off solving
his own murder.

1226
01:20:38,007 --> 01:20:41,053
Oh, that is genius.

1227
01:20:41,184 --> 01:20:42,663
Why didn't I think of that?

1228
01:20:50,193 --> 01:20:51,716
VALLON: <i> How long</i> 
<i>till he gets here?</i>

1229
01:20:51,847 --> 01:20:54,066
WOMAN: <i> Five minutes.</i>All right.

1230
01:20:54,197 --> 01:20:55,633
Johnny, you stay
on these monitors.

1231
01:20:55,763 --> 01:20:56,852
JOHNNY: What happened?

1232
01:20:58,418 --> 01:21:00,856
Some idiot used
an unencrypted phone.

1233
01:21:02,466 --> 01:21:03,336
MARCUS: Shit.

1234
01:21:12,041 --> 01:21:13,042
All right, everyone,
listen up!

1235
01:21:13,477 --> 01:21:15,087
He's coming.

1236
01:21:15,218 --> 01:21:17,873
He leaves alive, you don't.

1237
01:21:19,222 --> 01:21:20,745
MAN: How do we stop him?

1238
01:21:22,399 --> 01:21:25,054
.50 caliber and above.
Aim for the head.

1239
01:21:34,977 --> 01:21:35,891
[BEEP]

1240
01:21:37,544 --> 01:21:39,111
This one's set.

1241
01:21:39,242 --> 01:21:40,591
Let's go. Go![BEEPING]

1242
01:21:40,721 --> 01:21:41,722
All right, move! Let's go!

1243
01:21:43,246 --> 01:21:44,900
Come on. Come on!

1244
01:21:46,814 --> 01:21:47,728
Ready to go!

1245
01:21:48,904 --> 01:21:49,905
They're all set.

1246
01:21:51,254 --> 01:21:52,385
[POWERING DOWN]

1247
01:21:56,868 --> 01:21:58,435
[MOTORCYCLE APPROACHING]

1248
01:22:00,393 --> 01:22:01,829
[GUNS COCKING]

1249
01:22:56,275 --> 01:22:56,972
[SCREAMS][SHELLS CLATTERING]

1250
01:23:18,210 --> 01:23:19,124
Finish it!

1251
01:23:25,696 --> 01:23:26,697
[GROANS]

1252
01:23:33,878 --> 01:23:35,010
You freak, die!

1253
01:23:44,715 --> 01:23:45,585
[SCREAMING]

1254
01:23:48,893 --> 01:23:50,155
[HEAVY FOOTSTEPS]

1255
01:24:18,575 --> 01:24:20,185
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

1256
01:24:24,450 --> 01:24:25,973
Watch out.

1257
01:24:26,104 --> 01:24:27,845
LEWIS: Need me
to call a doctor?

1258
01:24:27,975 --> 01:24:29,542
Come on, Jack.
You're gonna like this.

1259
01:24:32,458 --> 01:24:33,764
What the hell
you doin' here?

1260
01:24:33,894 --> 01:24:35,113
Y'all gonna play
good cop, bad cop?

1261
01:24:35,244 --> 01:24:37,289
Nah, Daniels.
Bad cop, RoboCop.

1262
01:24:40,031 --> 01:24:43,252
ROBOCOP: I've recovered
26 guns from
Vallon's warehouse.

1263
01:24:43,382 --> 01:24:46,037
Thirteen serial numbers
match weapons
missing from Evidence.

1264
01:24:46,168 --> 01:24:47,734
And I got your prints
all over 'em.

1265
01:24:47,865 --> 01:24:49,171
This is bullshit.

1266
01:24:49,301 --> 01:24:51,216
ROBOCOP: I also
have CCTV footage

1267
01:24:51,347 --> 01:24:53,479
of you and Vallon
the same day
he tried to kill me.

1268
01:24:53,610 --> 01:24:56,091
VALLON: <i> So put him</i> 
<i>on the payroll. Why</i> 
<i>we talkin' about this?</i>

1269
01:24:56,221 --> 01:24:59,094
DANIELS: <i> It won't work.</i> 
<i>Now that his partner got hit,</i> 
<i>he's never gonna let it go.</i>

1270
01:24:59,224 --> 01:25:00,486
VALLON: <i> What is that?</i>LAKE: <i> Lewis' hospital.</i>

1271
01:25:00,617 --> 01:25:02,401
 <i>Murphy's dropping by</i> 
<i>this afternoon.</i>

1272
01:25:02,532 --> 01:25:05,361
 <i>I kill a cop, I'm lookin'</i> 
<i>over my shoulder...</i>

1273
01:25:05,491 --> 01:25:08,146
You know what they do
to cops in prison, man?

1274
01:25:08,277 --> 01:25:10,105
Being locked up
with the same dudes
you put in there?

1275
01:25:14,109 --> 01:25:15,153
How long you think
before he gives you up?

1276
01:25:16,198 --> 01:25:17,155
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

1277
01:25:19,244 --> 01:25:21,768
Don't shoot me. Okay?

1278
01:25:23,161 --> 01:25:25,903
I swear to Christ.
It was Dean.

1279
01:25:26,033 --> 01:25:28,166
She helped pull those guns.
Just don't shoot me.

1280
01:25:30,342 --> 01:25:32,127
Thank you
for your cooperation.

1281
01:25:33,215 --> 01:25:34,346
[SCREAMS]

1282
01:25:34,477 --> 01:25:35,782
You can cuff him now, Jack.

1283
01:25:45,357 --> 01:25:46,793
Now I know why we
couldn't get an arrest.

1284
01:25:48,578 --> 01:25:50,319
'Cause Vallon was protected
from up on high.

1285
01:25:50,449 --> 01:25:52,016
Alex, I can explain.

1286
01:25:52,886 --> 01:25:54,192
You tipped
him off today.

1287
01:25:54,323 --> 01:25:55,541
Come on, man.
Don't do this.

1288
01:25:55,672 --> 01:25:57,630
You tried to kill me twice.

1289
01:25:57,761 --> 01:26:01,025
I trusted you.
And you destroyed my family.

1290
01:26:01,156 --> 01:26:02,069
Confess.

1291
01:26:03,593 --> 01:26:05,116
Now, in front of everyone.

1292
01:26:05,247 --> 01:26:06,161
Confess!

1293
01:26:10,252 --> 01:26:11,253
[PEOPLE GASP]

1294
01:26:16,127 --> 01:26:17,259
What happened?

1295
01:26:17,389 --> 01:26:19,435
Tin Man is down.
Had to be done.

1296
01:26:19,565 --> 01:26:20,914
 <i>Why?</i>

1297
01:26:21,045 --> 01:26:22,264
Product shot a corrupt cop.

1298
01:26:22,394 --> 01:26:23,874
Two more seconds,
the chief's brains

1299
01:26:24,004 --> 01:26:26,529
would've been splattered
across the 6:00 news.

1300
01:26:26,659 --> 01:26:28,139
We got anything on her?

1301
01:26:28,270 --> 01:26:30,185
Well, she's the Chief of
the Detroit Police Department.

1302
01:26:30,315 --> 01:26:32,056
What do you think?

1303
01:26:35,973 --> 01:26:37,192
You know what?

1304
01:26:39,150 --> 01:26:41,848
This might actually
tip this thing
right into the net.

1305
01:26:48,855 --> 01:26:52,076
NOVAK ON TV: 
<i>Alex, I don't know</i> 
<i>if you can hear me.</i>

1306
01:26:52,207 --> 01:26:55,514
 <i>But tonight,</i> 
<i>you uncovered a nest of vipers</i>

1307
01:26:55,645 --> 01:26:58,256
 <i>inside</i> 
<i>the Detroit Police Department.</i>

1308
01:26:58,387 --> 01:27:02,129
 <i>And in so doing,</i> 
<i>you shed light</i> 
<i>on an invaluable truth.</i>

1309
01:27:03,087 --> 01:27:04,654
Even the police,

1310
01:27:04,784 --> 01:27:08,266
the men and women
who swore to keep us safe,

1311
01:27:09,180 --> 01:27:10,355
they can be bribed.

1312
01:27:11,400 --> 01:27:14,054
They can be bought.

1313
01:27:16,143 --> 01:27:19,843
Machines, however,
are corruption free.

1314
01:27:21,366 --> 01:27:23,455
Americans could be
living in a country

1315
01:27:23,586 --> 01:27:26,937
where law enforcement
is not only efficient,

1316
01:27:27,067 --> 01:27:28,243
but incorruptible.

1317
01:27:30,027 --> 01:27:32,116
Thank you, Alex,
for all you've done.

1318
01:27:32,247 --> 01:27:34,684
And for all that you are.

1319
01:27:34,814 --> 01:27:38,383
 <i>Detective Murphy</i> 
<i>is currently</i> 
<i>in critical condition.</i>

1320
01:27:38,514 --> 01:27:41,386
Our doctors
are working ceaselessly

1321
01:27:41,517 --> 01:27:44,041
but, at this time,
it is unclear
if he will survive.

1322
01:27:44,171 --> 01:27:45,695
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

1323
01:27:45,825 --> 01:27:47,349
KELLY: <i> Ms. Kline,</i> 
<i>how do you think the attempt</i>

1324
01:27:47,479 --> 01:27:49,481
 <i>on Detective</i> 
<i>Alex Murphy's life</i>

1325
01:27:49,612 --> 01:27:51,570
 <i>will affect tomorrow's vote</i> 
<i>for the Dreyfus Act?</i>

1326
01:27:51,701 --> 01:27:53,746
LIZ: <i> At this time,</i> 
<i>Omnicorp's sole concern</i>

1327
01:27:53,877 --> 01:27:55,270
 <i>is the full recovery</i> 
<i>of Detective Murphy.</i>

1328
01:27:56,880 --> 01:27:59,230
 <i>How many times</i> 
<i>does Detective Murphy</i>

1329
01:27:59,361 --> 01:28:02,364
 <i>have to give his life</i> 
<i>for his country?</i>

1330
01:28:02,494 --> 01:28:07,369
 <i>I sincerely hope the Senate</i> 
<i>makes the right vote tomorrow</i>

1331
01:28:07,499 --> 01:28:11,242
 <i>so that Alex Murphy's</i> 
<i>sacrifices will not</i> 
<i>have been in vain.</i>

1332
01:28:16,726 --> 01:28:18,597
OHIO SENATOR ON TV: 
<i>Senator Dreyfus is my friend.</i>

1333
01:28:18,728 --> 01:28:21,513
 <i>He has been</i> 
<i>my mentor and my strength</i>

1334
01:28:21,644 --> 01:28:24,777
 <i>in times of difficulty</i> 
<i>on this floor.</i>

1335
01:28:24,908 --> 01:28:28,128
 <i>But despite all that,</i> 
<i>I work for the state of Ohio,</i>

1336
01:28:28,259 --> 01:28:30,957
 <i>and the safety of its citizens</i> 
<i>is my top priority.</i>

1337
01:28:31,088 --> 01:28:32,568
 <i>So I vote yes.</i>

1338
01:28:32,698 --> 01:28:35,135
 <i>The Dreyfus Act</i> 
<i>must be repealed.</i>

1339
01:28:35,266 --> 01:28:37,703
That's us ahead,
39 to 10.

1340
01:28:37,834 --> 01:28:40,663
I spoke to the Senate
liaison and it looks
like it's in the bag,

1341
01:28:40,793 --> 01:28:43,448
but we still have to
tread carefully
with the politicians.

1342
01:28:43,579 --> 01:28:45,189
[NOVAK ELEMENT THEME SONG
PLAYING ON TV]

1343
01:28:45,320 --> 01:28:47,713
KELLY: <i> We're here live</i> 
<i>at DPD headquarters</i>

1344
01:28:47,844 --> 01:28:50,020
 <i>where moments ago,</i> 
<i>Clara Murphy made</i> 
<i>a shocking statement.</i>

1345
01:28:50,150 --> 01:28:52,283
POPE: What the hell?

1346
01:28:52,414 --> 01:28:56,331
 <i>Omnicorp has denied</i> 
<i>me and my son</i> 
<i>access to Alex for weeks.</i>

1347
01:28:57,114 --> 01:29:00,639
 <i>I demand to know why.</i>

1348
01:29:00,770 --> 01:29:04,861
 <i>This treatment is inhuman</i> 
<i>and somebody needs to be</i> 
<i>held accountable.</i>

1349
01:29:06,210 --> 01:29:08,255
Oh, we're fucked.

1350
01:29:08,386 --> 01:29:09,605
No, we only need 12 votes.

1351
01:29:09,735 --> 01:29:11,476
She shouldn't make
much difference.

1352
01:29:11,607 --> 01:29:13,783
POPE: Yeah, but what about
after the vote?

1353
01:29:13,913 --> 01:29:15,741
I mean, those two should
not be allowed contact.

1354
01:29:15,872 --> 01:29:18,309
If she starts
putting ideas in his head...

1355
01:29:18,440 --> 01:29:21,051
Bring her in.
I'll handle the explanation.

1356
01:29:21,181 --> 01:29:22,748
POPE: And what about Alex?

1357
01:29:22,879 --> 01:29:25,751
You know, unfortunately,
we can't just keep him on ice.

1358
01:29:25,882 --> 01:29:28,232
LIZ: The shooting
at the station spooked
some of the politicians.

1359
01:29:28,363 --> 01:29:31,104
They're our clients.
We have to take care of them.

1360
01:29:31,235 --> 01:29:34,456
They're fine when a machine
is lowering the murder rate,

1361
01:29:34,586 --> 01:29:37,763
but when a man is
investigating city politics,
they get nervous.

1362
01:29:37,894 --> 01:29:40,070
All right. First off,
it's not a man, okay?

1363
01:29:40,200 --> 01:29:42,289
It's property of Omnicorp.

1364
01:29:42,420 --> 01:29:44,596
And politics are
the least of your concern.

1365
01:29:44,727 --> 01:29:46,468
I mean, this thing
solved its own murder.

1366
01:29:46,598 --> 01:29:48,557
How long till it
realizes you haven't been
on the level with it?

1367
01:29:48,687 --> 01:29:50,428
POPE: If that happens,

1368
01:29:50,559 --> 01:29:53,039
every journalist
in this country
is dying to speak to him.

1369
01:29:53,170 --> 01:29:55,564
I mean, we created a hero.

1370
01:29:55,694 --> 01:29:57,914
What happens
when he opens his mouth?

1371
01:30:01,613 --> 01:30:03,136
What's bigger than a hero?

1372
01:30:15,105 --> 01:30:16,106
Dead hero.

1373
01:30:20,589 --> 01:30:22,417
Get me Dr. Norton.

1374
01:30:31,556 --> 01:30:34,472
What is this, Raymond?

1375
01:30:34,603 --> 01:30:38,215
You have Mattox spying on me
and now this bullshit
about a "critical condition"?

1376
01:30:38,345 --> 01:30:40,739
You know and I know
Alex is fine!

1377
01:30:40,870 --> 01:30:42,045
Calm down.

1378
01:30:42,175 --> 01:30:43,873
Dennett.

1379
01:30:44,003 --> 01:30:45,352
Your work is so good,
I don't...

1380
01:30:45,483 --> 01:30:46,484
Well, now,
this is not about my work!

1381
01:30:46,615 --> 01:30:48,530
You saw the woman on TV!

1382
01:30:48,660 --> 01:30:50,445
This has to stop!

1383
01:30:52,577 --> 01:30:54,753
You're right.

1384
01:30:54,884 --> 01:30:57,234
But let me
ask you something, Dennett.

1385
01:30:57,364 --> 01:30:59,541
What kind of life
have we really
given Alex Murphy?

1386
01:30:59,671 --> 01:31:03,414
He's never gonna be
a normal man,
a father, a husband.

1387
01:31:03,545 --> 01:31:06,156
By the time we put
the other units on the
street, he's just...

1388
01:31:06,286 --> 01:31:07,287
Dennett.

1389
01:31:08,201 --> 01:31:09,115
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

1390
01:31:09,246 --> 01:31:10,465
Let's face it.

1391
01:31:11,596 --> 01:31:12,945
We failed him.

1392
01:31:14,599 --> 01:31:16,819
We failed Alex Murphy.

1393
01:31:16,949 --> 01:31:18,560
But I want you
to think about
the bigger picture

1394
01:31:18,690 --> 01:31:20,431
because that's what
we're talking about.

1395
01:31:20,562 --> 01:31:22,781
The work you've done
with him is gonna be
studied for decades.

1396
01:31:22,912 --> 01:31:25,392
You've changed
the face of history, Dennett.

1397
01:31:25,523 --> 01:31:29,222
No policeman is ever
going to die in
the line of duty again

1398
01:31:30,267 --> 01:31:31,486
because of you.

1399
01:31:33,488 --> 01:31:34,445
You think about that.

1400
01:31:43,498 --> 01:31:47,414
I want that family
taken care of

1401
01:31:47,545 --> 01:31:48,807
beyond their wildest dreams.

1402
01:31:48,938 --> 01:31:51,680
We owe them that.I agree.

1403
01:31:51,810 --> 01:31:55,553
I want full funding.
Ten years.

1404
01:31:55,684 --> 01:31:57,120
New staff, all my own people.

1405
01:31:57,250 --> 01:31:58,513
Fantastic.

1406
01:31:59,514 --> 01:32:00,427
Deal.

1407
01:32:11,003 --> 01:32:12,788
Hey. What's going on?

1408
01:32:12,918 --> 01:32:14,572
Security's here.
They're clearing everyone out.

1409
01:32:14,703 --> 01:32:16,661
They're not waking him up.

1410
01:32:16,792 --> 01:32:18,663
Whatever you do,
don't leave him alone.

1411
01:32:18,794 --> 01:32:19,664
What do you mean
they're not waking him up?

1412
01:32:22,362 --> 01:32:23,494
SENATE LEADER ON TV: 
<i>The voting period has ended.</i>

1413
01:32:23,625 --> 01:32:25,888
 <i>The clerks have</i> 
<i>tabulated the results.</i>

1414
01:32:26,018 --> 01:32:28,194
 <i>The yeas are 63.</i>

1415
01:32:28,325 --> 01:32:31,415
 <i>The nays are 22.</i>

1416
01:32:31,546 --> 01:32:33,722
 <i>A majority of senators have</i> 
<i>voted in the affirmative.</i>

1417
01:32:33,852 --> 01:32:37,377
 <i>The Dreyfus Act has been</i> 
<i>repealed by Congress.</i>

1418
01:32:37,508 --> 01:32:38,509
[PEOPLE APPLAUDING]

1419
01:32:41,686 --> 01:32:42,992
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

1420
01:32:43,122 --> 01:32:45,255
God, you guys are slow,
like a bunch of girls.

1421
01:32:45,385 --> 01:32:46,473
This is Mattox.

1422
01:32:46,604 --> 01:32:47,910
SELLARS: <i> Dennett's on board.</i>

1423
01:32:48,040 --> 01:32:49,476
It's about time.

1424
01:32:54,656 --> 01:32:55,657
Call it.

1425
01:32:56,527 --> 01:32:57,615
 <i>Get it done.</i>

1426
01:32:59,008 --> 01:33:00,226
My pleasure.

1427
01:33:02,577 --> 01:33:04,100
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

1428
01:33:09,540 --> 01:33:11,760
Mrs. Murphy...You can come here
as much as you want.

1429
01:33:11,890 --> 01:33:15,024
You can threaten me.
You can sue me.
You can take my home.

1430
01:33:15,154 --> 01:33:17,983
But I am not gonna stop
till I see my husband.
Do you understand that?

1431
01:33:18,114 --> 01:33:20,595
Mr. Sellars would
very much like to see you.

1432
01:33:22,466 --> 01:33:24,555
Is Alex okay?

1433
01:33:24,686 --> 01:33:27,384
He has important information
to share with you.
Will you accompany me?

1434
